Libraries

JavaScript Libraries

     * [https://github.com/graphql/graphql-js]GraphQL.js - A reference
       implementation of GraphQL for JavaScript.
     * [https://github.com/graphql/express-graphql]express-graphql -
       GraphQL Express Middleware.
     * [https://github.com/chentsulin/koa-graphql]koa-graphql - GraphQL
       Koa Middleware.
     * [https://github.com/SimonDegraeve/hapi-graphql]hapi-graphql -
       Create a GraphQL HTTP server with Hapi.
     * [https://github.com/graphql/codemirror-graphql]codemirror-graphql -
       GraphQL mode and helpers for CodeMirror.
     * [https://github.com/devknoll/graphql-schema]graphql-schema - Create
       GraphQL schemas with a fluent/chainable interface.
     * [https://github.com/mickhansen/graphql-sequelize]graphql-sequelize
       - Sequelize helpers for GraphQL.
     * [https://github.com/Glavin001/graphql-sequelize-crud]graphql-sequel
       ize-crud - Automatically generate queries and mutations from
       Sequelize models.
     * [https://github.com/RisingStack/graffiti]graffiti - Node.js GraphQL
       ORM.
     * [https://github.com/RisingStack/graffiti-mongoose]graffiti-mongoose
       - Mongoose (MongoDB) adapter for graffiti (Node.js GraphQL ORM).
     * [https://github.com/ooflorent/babel-plugin-graphql]babel-plugin-gra
       phql - Babel plugin that compile GraphQL tagged template strings.
     * [https://github.com/gyzerok/adrenaline]adrenaline - React bindings
       for Redux with Relay in mind.
     * [https://github.com/brysgo/graphql-bookshelf]graphql-bookshelf -
       Some help defining GraphQL schema around BookshelfJS models.
     * [https://github.com/weyoss/graphql-bookshelfjs]graphql-bookshelfjs
       - A simple bridge between your graphql queries and your bookshelf
       models, perform batched and optimised queries.
     * [https://github.com/matthewmueller/graph.ql]graph.ql - Faster and
       simpler technique for creating and querying GraphQL schemas.
     * [https://github.com/kennetpostigo/react-reach]react-reach - A
       library to communicate with Graphql through Redux
     * [https://github.com/kadirahq/lokka]Lokka - Simple JavaScript client
       for GraphQL, which you can use anywhere.
     * [http://strapi.io/documentation/graphql]Strapi - Open-source
       Node.js framework that supports "GraphQL" out of the box.
     * [https://github.com/larsbs/graysql]GraysQL - A GraphQL manager and
       loader.
     * [https://github.com/larsbs/graysql-orm-loader]graysql-orm-loader -
       A GraysQL extension to load a GraphQL schema from an ORM.
     * [https://github.com/almilo/annotated-graphql]Annotated GraphQL -
       Proof of Concept for annotations in GraphQL (i.e.: transform an
       existing REST api into a GraphQL endpoint).
     * [https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client]Apollo Client - A
       well-documented GraphQL client. Has React and Angular bindings.
     * [https://github.com/apollographql/graphql-tools]graphql-tools -
       Tool library for building and maintaining GraphQL-JS servers.
     * [https://github.com/apollographql/graphql-anywhere]graphql-anywhere
       - Run a GraphQL query anywhere, against any data, with no schema.
     * [https://github.com/apollographql/graphql-tag]graphql-tag - A
       JavaScript template literal tag that parses GraphQL queries.
     * [https://github.com/julienvincent/modelizr]modelizr - A library for
       simplifying the process of writing GraphQL queries, mocking them
       and normalizing their responses.
     * [https://github.com/Akryum/vue-apollo]vue-apollo - Vue integration
       for apollo.
     * [https://github.com/fenos/graphql-thinky]graphql-thinky - Build an
       optimized GraphQL schema from Thinky RethinkDB models.
     * [https://github.com/MikeBild/graphql-pouch]graphql-pouch - A
       GraphQL-API runtime on top of PouchDB created by GraphQL shorthand
       notation as a self contained service with CouchDB synchronization.
     * [https://github.com/almilo/gql-tools]gql-tools - Tool library with
       CLI for schema generation and manipulation.
     * [https://github.com/excitement-engineer/graphql-iso-date]graphql-is
       o-date - A GraphQL date scalar type to be used with GraphQL.js.
       This scalar represents a date in the ISO 8601 format YYYY-MM-DD.
     * [https://github.com/nodkz/graphql-compose]graphql-compose - Tool
       which allows you to construct flexible graphql schema from
       different data sources via plugins.
     * [https://github.com/mwilliamson/node-graphjoiner]node-graphjoiner -
       Create GraphQL APIs using joins, SQL or otherwise.
     * [https://github.com/gucheen/FetchQL]FetchQL - GraphQL query client
       with Fetch
     * [https://github.com/stems/join-monster]Join Monster - A
       GraphQL-to-SQL query execution layer for batch data fetching.
     * [https://github.com/graphql-community/create-graphql]Create-GraphQL
       - Command-line utility to build production-ready servers with
       GraphQL.
     * [https://github.com/lucasbento/graphql-pokemon]GraphQL-Pokémon -
       Get information of a Pokémon with GraphQL!
     * [https://github.com/graphql-factory]graphql-factory - Create
       GraphQL types from JSON definitions
     * [https://chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/chromeiql/fkkiamalmpiidk
       ljmicmjfbieiclmeij]ChromeiQL - Chrome extension to use GraphiQL
       anywhere
     * [https://github.com/ejoebstl/graphql-auto-mutation]graphql-auto-mut
       ation - Automatically generates functions for mutations specified
       in a GraphQL schema.
     * [https://github.com/graphitejs/graphitejs]GraphiteJS - Full stack
       GraphQL framework.
     * [https://github.com/tallyb/loopback-graphql]loopback-graphql -
       GraphQL Server for Loopback.
     * [https://github.com/octet-stream/parasprite]parasprite - Describe
       your GraphQL schema using chainable interface.
     * [https://github.com/f/graphql.js]GraphQL.js - JavaScript GraphQL
       Client for Browser and Node.js Usage
     * [https://github.com/arangodb/graphql-sync]graphql-sync -
       Promise-free wrapper to GraphQL.js for synchronous environments
     * [https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-fetch]apollo-fetch -
       Lightweight GraphQL client that supports custom fetch functions,
       middleware, and afterware
     * [https://github.com/spikenail/spikenail]Spikenail - Node.js
       framework for building GraphQL API almost without coding.
     * [https://github.com/AEB-labs/graphql-weaver]graphql-weaver - A tool
       to combine, link and transform GraphQL schemas; combine multiple
       GraphQL servers into one API.
     * [https://github.com/APIs-guru/graphql-lodash]graphql-lodash - Data
       manipulation for GraphQL queries with lodash syntax.
     * [https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-angular]apollo-angular -
       Angular integration for Apollo.
     * [https://github.com/lucasconstantino/graphql-resolvers]graphql-reso
       lvers - Resolver composition library for GraphQL.
     * [https://github.com/thebigredgeek/apollo-resolvers]apollo-resolvers
       - Expressive and composable resolvers for Apollo Server and
       graphql-tools.
     * [https://github.com/thebigredgeek/apollo-errors]apollo-errors -
       Machine-readable custom errors for Apollo Server.
     * [https://github.com/helfer/graphql-disable-introspection]graphql-di
       sable-introspection - Graphql Disable Introspection
     * [https://github.com/arackaf/mongo-graphql-starter]mongo-graphql-sta
       rter - Flexible and robust Mongo based resolvers for Node.
     * [https://github.com/imolorhe/altair]altair-express-middleware - An
       express middleware for mounting an instance of Altair GraphQL
       client.

Relay Related

     * [https://github.com/facebook/relay]relay - Relay is a JavaScript
       framework for building data-driven React applications.
     * [https://github.com/graphql/graphql-relay-js]graphql-relay-js - A
       library to help construct a graphql-js server supporting
       react-relay.
     * [https://github.com/MattMcFarland/sequelize-relay]sequelize-relay -
       Serverside library that connects sequelize and graphql-relay-js
       together.
     * [https://github.com/graphcool/babel-plugin-react-relay]babel-plugin
       -react-relay - Babel Plugin for Relay with support for JSON &
       graphql-js schemas and URL endpoints.
     * [https://www.npmjs.com/package/babel-relay-plugin]babel-relay-plugi
       n - Babel Relay Plugin for transpiling GraphQL queries for use with
       Relay.
     * [https://github.com/relay-tools/react-router-relay]react-router-rel
       ay - Relay integration for React Router.
     * [https://github.com/relay-tools/relay-local-schema]relay-local-sche
       ma - Use Relay without a GraphQL server.
     * [https://github.com/acdlite/relay-sink]relay-sink - Use Relay to
       fetch and store data outside of a React component.
     * [https://github.com/acdlite/recompose/tree/master/src/packages/reco
       mpose-relay]recompose-relay - Recompose helpers for Relay.
     * [https://github.com/larsbs/graysql#Graylay]Graylay - A GraysQL
       extension to create a Relay compatible Schema.
     * [https://github.com/apollographql/apollo-client]Apollo Client - A
       simple alternative to Relay, comes with React and Angular bindings.
     * [https://github.com/nodkz/react-relay-network-layer]react-relay-net
       work-layer - A network layer for Relay with query batching and
       middleware support (urlThunk, retryThunk, auth, defer and other).
     * [https://github.com/edvinerikson/relay-subscriptions]relay-subscrip
       tions - Subscription support for Relay.
     * [https://github.com/alex-cory/portfolio]Portfolio Relay Example -
       An example website that fetches data from various apis and uses
       Relay and GraphQL to feed the data to React components!
     * [https://github.com/lucasbento/react-relay-pokemon]Relay Pokédex -
       Project using GraphQL Pokémon to show how powerful Relay is.
     * [https://github.com/ntkme/vue-relay]vue-relay - A framework for
       building GraphQL-driven Vue.js applications.

TypeScript Libraries

     * [https://github.com/19majkel94/type-graphql]TypeGraphQL - Create
       GraphQL schema and resolvers with TypeScript, using classes and
       decorators!
     * [http://vesper-framework.com/]Vesper - NodeJS framework that helps
       you to create scalable, maintainable, extensible, declarative and
       fast GraphQL-based server applications.
     * [https://github.com/calebmer/graphql-strong]graphql-strong - Define
       your GraphQL schemas with confidence that your values are correct.
     * [https://github.com/3VLINC/graphql-to-typescript]graphql-to-typescr
       ipt - Compiles GraphQL files into an importable typescript module
       with type definitions
     * [https://github.com/Quramy/graphql-decorator]graphql-decorator -
       Helps to build GraphQL schema with TypeScript.
     * [https://github.com/indigotech/graphql-schema-decorator]graphql-sch
       ema-decorator - This package makes possible the use of decorators
       to define a GraphQL schema.
     * [https://github.com/vichyssoise/graphql-typescript]graphql-typescri
       pt - Define and build GraphQL Schemas using typed classes
     * [https://github.com/prismake/typegql]typegql - Create GraphQL
       schema with type-safe class decorators.

Ruby Libraries

     * [https://github.com/rmosolgo/graphql-ruby]graphql-ruby - Ruby
       implementation of Facebook's GraphQL.
     * [https://github.com/Shopify/graphql-parser]graphql-parser - A small
       ruby gem wrapping the libgraphqlparser C library for parsing
       GraphQL.
     * [https://github.com/github/graphql-client]graphql-client - A Ruby
       library for declaring, composing and executing GraphQL queries.
     * [https://github.com/Shopify/graphql-batch]graphql-batch - A query
       batching executor for the graphql gem.
     * [https://github.com/exaspark/batch-loader]batch-loader - A powerful
       tool to avoid N+1 queries without extra dependencies or primitives.
     * [https://github.com/exAspArk/graphql-guard]graphql-guard - A simple
       field-level authorization for the graphql gem.

PHP Libraries

     * [https://github.com/webonyx/graphql-php]graphql-php - A PHP port of
       GraphQL reference implementation.
     * [https://github.com/ivome/graphql-relay-php]graphql-relay-php -
       Relay helpers for GraphQL & PHP.
     * [https://github.com/api-platform/api-platform]API Platform - API
       framework compatible with Symfony having native GraphQL support.
     * [https://github.com/Folkloreatelier/laravel-graphql]laravel-graphql
       - Facebook GraphQL for Laravel 5.
     * [https://github.com/nuwave/laravel-graphql-relay]laravel-graphql-re
       lay - A Laravel library to help construct a server supporting
       react-relay.
     * [https://github.com/4rthem/graphql-mapper]graphql-mapper - This
       library allows to build a GraphQL schema based on your model.
     * [https://github.com/suribit/GraphQLBundle]graphql-bundle - GraphQL
       Bundle for Symfony 2.
     * [https://github.com/overblog/GraphQLBundle]overblog/graphql-bundle
       - This bundle provides tools to build a complete GraphQL server in
       your Symfony App. Supports react-relay.
     * [https://github.com/Youshido/GraphQL]GraphQL - Well documented PHP
       implementation with no dependencies.
     * [https://github.com/Youshido/GraphQLBundle]GraphQL Symfony Bundle
       - GraphQL Bundle for the Symfony 3 (supports 2.6+).
     * [https://github.com/wp-graphql/wp-graphql]WPGraphQL - WordPress
       plugin that exposes a Relay compliant GraphQL endpoint
     * [https://github.com/tim-field/graphql-wp]graphql-wp - a WordPress
       plugin that exposes a GraphQL endpoint.
     * [https://www.symfony.fi/entry/graphql-bundle-adds-protocol-support-
       to-ez-platform-symfony-cms]eZ Platform GraphQL Bundle - GraphQL
